{
  "id": "helix-shadcn-tokens",
  "title": "Align shadcn/ui theme with @helix/tokens design tokens",
  "category": "frontend",
  "description": "The admin app should use the same design language as the Helix web component library. This requires bridging @helix/tokens CSS custom properties (--hx-*) to shadcn's expected CSS variable format (--background, --foreground, --primary, etc.).\n\n## What to do\n\n1. Audit `@helix/tokens/src/tokens.json` to understand available token values\n2. Create `apps/admin/src/styles/tokens-bridge.css` that maps:\n   - `--primary` → `@helix/tokens` primary color value\n   - `--secondary` → secondary color\n   - `--destructive` → error/danger color\n   - `--muted` → subtle background\n   - `--background`, `--foreground` → surface/text tokens\n   - `--radius` → border radius token\n   - `--ring` → focus ring color\n3. Import the bridge file in `apps/admin/src/app/globals.css`\n4. Test in both light and dark mode if dark mode is supported\n5. Update `apps/admin/src/app/layout.tsx` to import tokens CSS\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- shadcn components visually match the Helix token palette\n- No hardcoded color values in the bridge file — all values reference `@helix/tokens`\n- Both themes work if dark mode is implemented\n- Admin app builds and renders correctly",
